storyInfo: The duel between Gambino and Capone is once again interrupted by Waai Fu and Jaye. The two Lungmen youths are committed to making the reckless Mafia pay the price. Meanwhile, the Rat King meets with an old friend at the cemetary.

attributes.content: 0:00 AM \ Dusty
Downtown Lungmen, Busy Street
Hey, you're doing the whole 'triad face' thing again, you know?
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: ...Welcome back. Did you look into those people for me?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: I came up with a rough sketch. As much as I'd like to bring these evildoers to justice, it looks like it's not going to be a one woman job.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: I may have to ask for help at the office.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: Seems they're not your run of the mill punks. And that Aak wasn't exactly forthcoming. He has to go and make everything so complicated...
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: I'm sorry, who?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Aak.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: Ah?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: ...His name is Aak.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: Oh... Okay, well, since it's not so simple,
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: I'll help out.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: ...You were listening, weren't you? A bunch of street thugs is one thing, but if we're dealing with a large-scale organized syndicate, we can't just go in there and start throwing punches.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: We have other options besides going in there and starting to throw punches, don't we?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Are you really going to nail me on semantics?
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: I'm not joking.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: ...Is Uncle Tung okay?
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: He wasn't hurt badly. But that's not the point.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Right. It's not. If this were just some underworld spat, I wouldn't get involved.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: But when I see the wicked strike the innocent before my very eyes, I can't sit idly by and let them run amok.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: ...Thanks. You've earned some finballs. On me.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: I don't need finballs...
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: By the way,
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: This business tonight has something to do with Penguin Logistics. They're not even trying to cover up their involvement.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: They're good people. They probably just got mixed up in it somehow.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: They've gotten 'mixed up in things somehow' dozens of times this year alone. They need to be a little more careful, and stop making trouble for everyone.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: If we run into them, we'll have to give them a warning.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: Sand Originium Arts. Hmph.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Guess the freak running Lungmen's underworld had to have some teeth to him.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Mr. Capone, you don't mean...?
attributes.name: Mafioso

attributes.content: He ain't the kinda guy you wanna piss off, capiche?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: The Rat King? But we're facing off against the boss, Penguin Logistics, and...
attributes.name: Mafioso

attributes.content: And half of Lungmen. Yeah, the outlook ain't so rosy. No room for mistakes.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: What're you doing, Mr. Capone? Put down the crossbow!
attributes.name: Mafioso

attributes.content: You thought going against the Family would be easy?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: I remember the face of every last man who agreed to follow me to Lungmen, who's ready to betray Gambino for the sake of survival.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: And you ain't one of 'em. Take a dirt nap, Gambino dog.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Get outta here.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Here I thought you were just an ungrateful cazzo. Now I see you learned to buy and sell men.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Who do you think taught me?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Sure as hell wasn't me.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: You earned my loyalty. Then you let me down harder than anything ever has. I won't make that same mistake.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: You know what betrayal means, don't you?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: It's Siracusa's greatest crime. But too bad for you, your honor and glory ain't worth shit in Lungmen.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Take it.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: ...the Jack of Spades?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: I told you. You deal too slow!
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: You're even slower with that sword, Gambino. You get hurt in your fight with the Penguins? Or are we openin' old wounds?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Seeing you turn coward like this makes me sick. I'm stuck thinkin' about how I should kill a traitor like you.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: You're the Joker here now.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: What's next? What're you gonna do? You take out Penguin Logistics? You take out the Rat King? You take out the LGD? You take out Wei Yenwu?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: You're dreaming. Why not fall asleep forever?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Don't worry, I'll send your ashes back to Siracusa. Maybe I'll have the old village grind your corpse up.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Woah, what're you...?!
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: ...What?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Sounds like we got party crashers.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: ...I shoulda killed you quicker. But now we gotta play host.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Stop 'em! Aagh! My toe...
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: What's this, kung fu?! Can't even touch her!
attributes.name: Mafioso B

attributes.content: They're unarmed, just get 'em... Oof!
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: ...Phew.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: So, it's you two?
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: I don't like to go around pickin' on weak little ladies, but...
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: You tore through my boys, walked right up to me, and you don't got a speck of dust on those pretty clothes of yours.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: You the Rat King's people?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: ...Were you in the slums?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: You broke up a fight between Sicilians and you got the balls to ask questions?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: ...Yeah. I'd say it was you two.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: This mook, argh——!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Are you just going to watch?
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: Don't get me wrong. It's always a good idea to borrow a knife to off somebody, but I gotta deal with this cazzo myself.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: On the other hand... You look like you're a handful.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: I think you should surrender. Really.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: Hah!
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: You're about as good as that wolf. Who knew the Rat King had cards like you up his sleeve!
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: What cards? What are you talking about? Just get down on the floor and turn yourself in!
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: Nng!
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Hey, I remember you. I met you before. You dressed up like a seafood salesman. Played like you were making finballs.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Funny. I never thought I'd have to give you a second look.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: No, I really am a... never mind.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Right now, just for tonight, I am what you think I am.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Hai-yah!
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: Hmph!
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: You gettin' beat by a girl over there, Gambino.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Oh I'm still gonna kill you. Wipe that smile off your face.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: ...You've been looking for chances to take a low blow, dirty fighter.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: How can you hope to win if you strike with the wrong part of your fist?
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: You will pay for the harm you have done.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: ...You had me wait so long just to bring me here?
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: What is this about? Are we looking at grave plots? You want to be my neighbor even in death?
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: After so many years in business, how do you keep such a sharp tongue?
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: I don't talk to my customers like this. But you're not a customer.
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: I'm hurt.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: ...This is Ah Faat's grave. You probably don't know him.
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: This one's Rascally Chan's, and over here is Fake Yama.
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: Then in the back is Old Wu and the Steel Psycho, plus Lucky On. Lucky On's family was rich, so he got the hillside plot.
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: So many.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: At least they're all neighbors. We should think about where we'll stay too.
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: I think it's still too early for that. Or are you trying to tell me you've got some terminal illness?
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: It's not early. We don't live long enough, so it always feels like we've been through tough times.
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: Like me. Our brothers gave their lives for us. But now that I've settled down, I look back and reflect on my life...
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: And nothing seems like that big a deal anymore. If there was anything really that big, I wouldn't be able to enjoy a peaceful life.
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: Oh my. Did selling finballs bring you such enlightenment?
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: Honestly, food price inflation is a lot more dangerous to me than the mob.
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: ...Dai Lo, won't you be my neighbor here? The Feng Shui is excellent, and I hear you get a better deal buying the plots in pairs.
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: Are you done?
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: I'm joking. It's a joke. Aiya. At least you have a daughter. I'm going to die alone.
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: You have all the kids in the slums with you, don't you? And that Ah Fil boy.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: But there's no blood. It makes a difference when you get old.
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: ...So you have to outlive me, a bit. Not too much. Just a bit. I'll wait for you down there.
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: Are you always looking for ways to needle me?
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: By the way, I'm meeting an old friend later tonight. Would you like to join us for a drink?
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: No thanks. I'm worried Ah Fil is off getting himself into trouble. I'd better look into it.
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: I'll look into it for you.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: And how many old friends do I have left? I think they're all down there.
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: You have one.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: I can't talk with the one called Wei. I've been dealing with him a long time. It would be very short-lived.
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: But you took a bullet for Wei Yenwu. It's why you can't walk straight anymore.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: You think I don't know? Feh, I don't want to talk about this. It always makes me feel wretched.
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: ...But at least Lungmen can walk straight. At least she's not wretched.
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: You're the same as you ever were. And I guess that's a good thing.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: If you've really seen enough of him, then you better be on your way.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: And even if he did see you, he probably wouldn't know what to say.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: You finally let me go, Lin, this poor old wounded man.
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: Mr. Tung.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: What's that?
attributes.name: Uncle Tung

attributes.content: Live a while longer. Sell some more finballs.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: Buy yourself a building, open a restaurant, take a few apprentices, and then maybe think about where to put your coffin. There's no rush.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: The Rat King still lives. It's not your turn to die yet.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: ...fine.
attributes.name: Uncle Tung
